The nucleotide sequences of N and M selected gene fragments showed more than 97% identity among the BToV isolates, except for the N genes of BRV-1 and BRV-2 (Table 3, Table 4
). The nucleotide sequences of the BToV S gene fragment showed lower identity than those of N and M, even among the domestic samples (Table 5
). Representative sequence data have been deposited in the nucleotide database (DNA Data Bank of Japan) and assigned the following accession numbers: K-567 (N: AB270904, M: AB270905, S: AB270906), K-629 (N: AB270907), K-637 (M: AB270908, S: AB270909), K-639 (S: AB270910), K-645 (M: AB270911), K-674 (N: AB270912, M: AB270913, S: AB270914), K-676 (M: AB270915, S: AB270916), K-683 (M: AB270917, S: AB270918), K-684 (S: AB270919).
